HEADWORD: Monophyletic
<hw>Mon`o*phy*let"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ of
one tribe, fr. <grk>mo`nos</grk> single + <?/ clan.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to a single family or stock, or
to development from a single common parent form; -- opposed to
<ant>polyphyletic</ant>; <as>as, <ex>monophyletic</ex>
origin</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monophyllous</ent>⟦br⟧
